<div class="ezEmbeddedPlayerDiv"></div>
<p>In today's always-on, Internet connected world, it's hard to imagine that a business wouldn't have a website&mdash;even a simple one. I've been traveling a lot lately for work and I've been surprised how many local businesses I've come across that do not have a website, making it much more difficult for me to get information about them.</p>
<p>As a result, today on <a href="http://video.wsav.com/v/46418895/one-pager.htm?q=tech+tuesday">WSAV Tech Tuesday</a>, I talk about&nbsp;<a href="http://onepagerapp.com">One Pager</a>, a web-based service that allows business owners to create simple, one-page websites without having to know graphic design or web coding. Given that so many people search for information from their mobile device, a basic website with you location and hours of operation is an absolute must. Thanks to One Pager, you don't have to break the bank in order to get a simple website.</p>
<p><iframe src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/25830918?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0&amp;color=ffffff" width="640" height="360" frameborder="0" webkitAllowFullScreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>
